text: Konnevesi is a municipality in Central Finland. About 2,850 people lived there in January 2014. The municipalities next to it are Hankasalmi, Laukaa, Rautalampi, Vesanto and Äänekoski. Konnevesi was established in 1922. The name comes from a lake called Lake Konnevesi. == Other websites == * Category:Municipalities of Central Finland Category:1922 establishments in Europe Category:1920s establishments in Finland
